My eyes are closing.

92
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:28,000
I have no idea what time it is.

93
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,240
I've lost track of time.

94
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:31,280
If I were to guess it,

95
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:33,120
I think it'd be morning soon.

96
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,760
It's been a long night!

97
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:40,106
(We believe the long nights
and the paths we walk under the stars)

98
00:07:40,107 --> 00:07:41,487
(will eventually blossom.)

99
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:48,680
One more take.

100
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,480
Let's do it one more time.

101
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,990
Do you find your character challenging?

102
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,440
It's way too challenging.

103
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:57,520
Mm.

104
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:58,360
After all,

105
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:01,000
this is my first time doing a role

106
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:03,160
with so many lines.

107
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:04,320
It's got too many lines?

108
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,320
To be honest, that's not the case.

109
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:08,200
I have to give a poker face throughout.

110
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:11,720
However, I need to make sure
my eyes and facial expression are on point.

111
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,000
It's all about being emotional.

112
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:15,960
It's okay.

113
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:17,210
Which is your most favorite character?

114
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,800
My favorite character? I...

115
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:21,320
In fact, I wonder what it'd feel like
to act as An Sha.

116
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:22,320
I'd love to give that a try.

117
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,190
I'd get to wear contact lens.

118
